                            <br/>
                <h3 class="card-title">Hopewell Furnace National Historic Site</h3>
                <br/>
                <p>Hopewell Furnace showcases an early American landscape of industrial operations from 1771-1883, Hopewell and other "iron plantations" laid the foundation for the transformation of the United States into an industrial giant for the time. The park's 848 acres and historic structures illustrate the business, technology and lifestyle of our growing nation.</p>
